International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Fri 19 Aug 2022 14:15 EDT
Source: Fox 8 News [abridged, edited]
https://fox8.com/news/two-cases-of-e-coli-confirmed-in-cuyahoga-county/


The Cuyahoga County Board of Health has confirmed 2 cases of _E. coli_ in Cuyahoga County on Friday [19 Aug 2022]. The board of health says the Ohio Department of Health (ODH) is investigating the cases -- 14 total statewide. The "fast-moving" _E. coli_ outbreak that was identified in Ohio and Michigan has infected nearly 30 people from an unknown source.

The CDC says the true number of sick people in this outbreak is likely higher than the number reported. The outbreak hasn't been linked to food yet. However, the CDC says some preliminary information indicates that the people who have been confirmed to be sick with this strain of _E. coli_ got it from the same food; investigators just don't know what that food is yet. ODH has not released information on the 2 Cuyahoga County cases, including age, gender or city.

[Byline: Cris Belle]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED

[It is not clear as yet if these cases in Cuyahoga County, Ohio, located in northeastern Ohio with Cleveland as the county seat, are related to the ongoing outbreak in Michigan and northwestern Ohio.

To clarify, _E. coli_ are common colonizers in the human intestinal tract that provide a number of useful functions. If escaping into the urinary tract or breaking the mucosal barriers of the gut, they can cause significant infections. The enterohemorrhagic _E. coli_, which produce Shiga toxin, are one of the pathotypes that are not part of the normal flora but, if acquired, can cause disease. - Mod.LL

